
# Conventional commit <type> must be one of the following:
# 
#   build     The build system or external dependencies (example scopes: vite, npm)
#   chore     Miscellaneous, maintenance, e.g. modifying .gitignore
#   ci        CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: Travis, Bamboo)
#   docs      Documentation only changes
#   feat      A new feature
#   fix       A bug fix
#   perf      A code change that improves performance
#   refactor  A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   style     Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
#   test      Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#
# A Breaking change can be part of commits of any type when <footer> contains: 
# 
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# 
# or, when `!` is appended after the type/scope:
#
#   feat!(<scope>): <description>
#
#